p of analytical theories from sociology, rhetoric, and public policy, we will develop a general framework for thinking about argument and the dynamics of the relationship between science, technology and the public. In addition, we will look to these fields for tools to assess specific instances of public debate and to complicate andor affirm the prevailing theories about their relationship.", "student_sets": [{"id": 896, "name": "undergraduate"}], "offering_tags": [{"name": "intermittent", "type": "INFO"}], "website": null, "instructors": [], "is_repeatable": false, "is_req_repeatable": false, "repeat_limit_attempts": null, "repeat_limit_credits": null, "catalog_levels": [], "skills": [{"name": "Sciences & Technologies", "slug": "sciences-technologies", "id": 10}, {"name": "Social Sciences", "slug": "social-sciences", "id": 12}, {"name": "General Sciences", "slug": "general-sciences", "id": 162}, {"name": "Political Sciences", "slug": "political-sciences", "id": 1260}], "attributes": [{"name": "discussion intensive", "id": 2, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "for non-majors", "id": 6, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "interdisciplinary", "id": 10, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "reading intensive", "id": 13, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "writing intensive", "id": 18, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "communication & presentation", "id": 19, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "diversity", "id": 3, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "information & data literacy", "id": 20, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "research", "id": 14, "type": "attribute"}, {"name": "equity & inclusion", "id": 23, "type": "attribute"}], "custom_fields": {"goals": "To have a deeper appreciation of the challenges faced by scientists and nonexpert audiences when they interface with one another", "key_topics": "rhetoric, science, public sphere, vaccination debate, AIDS denialism, climate change, scientific expertise", "prerequisite_knowledge": null, "assessment_structure": "Participation in in-class and online 